Third-party components
======================

OpenTabletDriver (LGPL-3.0)
  https://github.com/OpenTabletDriver/OpenTabletDriver
  Used as the tablet driver: OpenTabletArtist bundles and talks to the OTD
  daemon and links its libraries (referenced via the external/OpenTabletDriver
  submodule). Licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0, which
  is compatible with this program's GPL-3.0 license.

VoiDPlugins — "Windows Ink" output-mode plugin (GPL-3.0)   [planned — see #319]
  https://github.com/Kuuuube/VoiDPlugins
  OpenTabletArtist plans to bundle the "Windows Ink" output-mode plugin from
  VoiDPlugins so it is available without a separate download (issue #319). When
  the plugin binary is bundled, the exact upstream release/commit it was built
  from will be recorded alongside it so the corresponding source is always
  available, as required by the GPL. VoiDPlugins is licensed under GPL-3.0.
